perators, review log template in place. | T2 | 5 | 6 | CCH-040 | — | - `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` describes cadence, how to ablate a rule, how to attach a review note<br/>- weekly review log at `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` with template entries (piece, date, felt-wrong symptom, suspected rule, ablation result, action)<br/>- tests: doc and template exist and link to the ablation CLI from CCH-010 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 33 | T-033 | Migrate Anthony's existing recorded music + handpicked field recordings into `samples/library/` with appropriate metadata. | T2 | 3 | 6 | CCS-032 | — | - `tools/sample_library_import.py` script reads a TOML manifest of source files + intended tags and inserts them into the library<br/>- supports both single-file and directory imports<br/>- preserves provenance (original path, captured-by) in `SampleRecord` extras<br/>- 100+ samples land in the library with accurate tags<br/>- tests cover the importer with a small fixture manifest |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Sprint 6 total:** ~18 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Sprint 6 total:** ~6 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ## Summary\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n - **Sprint 1 (Versioning System):** 10 tasks, ~30 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Sprint 2 (Quality Scoring):** 8 tasks, ~24 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Sprint 3 (Improvement Engine Hardening):** 10 tasks, ~30 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Sprint 2 (Quality Scoring):** 3 tasks, ~12 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Sprint 3 (Improvement Engine Hardening):** 10 tasks, ~36 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n - **Sprint 5 (Library & CRUD Polish):** 9 tasks, ~27 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Sprint 6 (Stretch Goals):** 3 tasks, ~18 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Sprint 6 (Stretch Goals):** 1 tasks, ~6 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Total: 40 tasks, ~129 hours**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Total: 33 tasks, ~111 hours**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260425T183959Zd_1777146814.log:3126:sdp/runner.log:2078:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_result\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-25T19:44:09.641Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command_1777146249360_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"diff --git a/sdp/implementation-plan.md b/sdp/implementation-plan.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nindex 4ed6434..5a9b512 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n--- a/sdp/implementation-plan.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+++ b/sdp/implementation-plan.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -1,9 +1,9 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-# PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer — Implementation Plan\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# PRD: CypherClaw Sampler — Granular Memory Voice as Primary Instrument — Implementation Plan\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Generated:** 2026-04-16T18:19:25.335643+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Generated:** 2026-04-25T18:39:59.551260+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n **Source:** PRD v1.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Total tasks:** 40\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Estimated effort:** ~129 hours\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Total tasks:** 33\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Estimated effort:** ~111 hours\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -15,16 +15,16 @@ Sprints are sequential. Tasks within a sprint can run in parallel unless a depen\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-001** [T1] Build a rule-ablation debugger that re-renders a score with selected rules disabled to localize expressive problems. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-002** [T1] Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-003** [T1] Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-004** [T1] Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-005** [T1] Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-006** [T1] Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-007** [T1] Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-008** [T1] Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-009** [T1] Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-010** [T1] Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-001** [T1] Implement buffer-management protocol: `OnSamplerLoad(record)` allocates scsynth buffer + reads WAV; `OnSamplerFree` releases buffer; LRU eviction at 64-buffer cap. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-002** [T1] Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-003** [T1] Implement `sampler_dispatch.py` that converts a `(SampleRecord, PerformanceIntent, params)` tuple into the OSC bundle (`/s_new sw_sampler ...` + buffer-pool acquire) and ships it to scsynth. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-004** [T1] Per-voice gate-controlled lifecycle: composer can `play_sampler(record, duration_sec)` for fire-and-forget OR `start_sampler(record) -> handle; stop_sampler(handle)` for sustained voices. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-005** [T1] Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-006** [T1] Implement `sample_capture_daemon.py` rolling 60-second buffers reading from `system:capture_1` (contact mic) and `system:capture_2` (room mic) via JACK. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-007** [T1] Implement interesting-moment detector: novelty (spectral flux) + transient density + RMS thresholds + duration-min/max gating. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-008** [T1] Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-009** [T1] Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **T-010** [T1] Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. (~3h)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n *Subtotal: ~30 hours*\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -32,47 +32,42 @@ Sprints are sequential. Tasks within a sprint can run in parallel unless a depen\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System), Sprint 1 (Quality Scoring)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-011** [T1] Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-012** [T1] Implement bounded reactive delta track in scheduler with per-parameter modulation caps. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-013** [T1] Expose aggregate-intention telemetry (global_energy/restraint/brightness) in operator diagnostics, never raw one-to-one mappings. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-014** [T1] Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **T-015** [T1] Build anti-pattern tests: quantization gho