ating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. | T1 | 7 | 3 | CCH-020 | T-011 | - all R1–R8 rules check `rule.applies_to(event.role)` before mutating the event<br/>- integration test: ostinato + melody passage renders with melody shaped and ostinato exactly quantized<br/>- gate test: passage where ostinato has non-zero timing_deviation_ms fails (indicates a rule leaked) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 20 | T-020 | Integrate partitura for phrase-feature extraction: harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, cadential detection, contour apex. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-021 | T-011 | - `render/features.py` wraps partitura load_score + per-phrase feature computation<br/>- features annotated onto Events during score-tree → Event-list conversion<br/>- harmonic_charge uses tonal-pitch-space distance (Lerdahl) normalized 0..1<br/>- tests on known-score fixtures verify expected feature values |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 21 | T-021 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-022 | T-011 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 22 | T-022 | Implement R10 Silence Budget: per-voice and per-section accumulators enforced at phrase boundaries. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-023 | T-011 | - `render/rules/silence_budget.py` maintains rest_budget += (target_density - actual_density)·dt per voice<br/>- when rest_budget exceeds threshold at phrase boundary, either extends breath (via R6) or drops next phrase to tacet<br/>- tests verify accumulator math, threshold trigger, and tacet