es well with the established harmonic planning utilities. No further actions required for this task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+codex\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+I found the existing verifier output saved under a different filename (`...@` with a space). I’ll verify escalation entries for T-019 and then create a fresh report at the exact required path, replacing naming mismatch and reflecting the latest test run.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+exec\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+/bin/zsh -lc 'cd /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw && rg -n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T-019|bootstrap_identity|FirstBootAnnouncer|startup\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" ESCALATIONS.md' in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ succeeded in 0ms:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+49:- **Details:** `AGENTS.md` asks for architecture/command/startup/changelog updates on orchestration changes, but this task also constrained edits to the bug-fix scope and those doc files already had unrelated local modifications. I limited the change set to the Ollama routing fix plus regression coverage and did not modify the product docs in this task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+100:- **Details:** The auto-generated hardening checks reference `bootstrap_identity` and `FirstBootAnnouncer`, which belong to the federation/identity subsystem. This task (self-critique and revision passes for music composition) has no relation to the startup identity flow. No new dependencies required; stdlib only.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+105:- **Details:** The auto-generated hardening checks reference `bootstrap_identity` and `FirstBootAnnouncer`, which belong to the federation/identity subsystem. This task (live-buffer and sample-bank abstractions) has no relation to the startup identity flow. No new dependencies required; stdlib only.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+127:- **Details:** Local verification passed after the provider-model escalation, but `sdp-cli tasks manual-verify` could not record the result because an active `sdp-cli run` process (PID 69939) owns `.sdp/run.lock`. The 