e(result, item.payload)`.\\n  4. Calls `mark_done(item.id)` on success.\\n  5. Catches exceptions and calls `mark_failed(item.id)`.\\n- Add an integration test `test_generation_queue_integration_worker_loop_success` using a fake client and fake storage that enqueues a request, runs `process_one()`, and verifies the row reaches `done`.\\n\\n# Edge Cases\\n- Dependencies like `cache` and `budget` do not exist yet, so they must be optional (`None` by default) and ignored if absent.\\n- `process_one` handles transient failures by calling `mark_failed()`.\\n\\n# Acceptance Criteria\\n1. `GenerationQueue` constructor accepts pipeline dependencies (`client`, `storage`, etc).\\n   - **VERIFY:** `pytest tests/test_generation_queue.py -k \\\"constructor\\\" -q`\\n2. `process_one` successfully processes a queued item, generates audio, stores it, and marks it done.\\n   - **VERIFY:** `pytest tests/test_generation_queue.py::test_integration_worker_loop_success -q`\\nEOF\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T03:57:28.800Z\",\"tool_name\":\"run_shell_command\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1777262248800_1\",\"parameters\":{\"command\":\"cat << 'EOF' > tests/test_integration_generation_queue.py\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom senseweave.generation.queue import GenerationQueue, QUEUED, DONE, FAILED\\nfrom senseweave.generation.storage import GenerationStorage\\nimport sqlite3\\n\\nclass FakeClient:\\n    def generate(self, request):\\n        return {\\\"audio_path\\\": \\\"/tmp/fake.wav\\\", \\\"cost_usd\\\": 0.01}\\n\\nclass FakeStorage:\\n    def save(self, result, req):\\n        return None\\n\\ndef test_integration_worker_loop_success(tmp_path: Path) -> None:\\n    db_path = tmp_path / \\\"queue.sqlite\\\"\\n    client = FakeClient()\\n    storage = FakeStorage()\\n    queue = GenerationQueue(db_path, client=client, storage=storage)\\n    \\n    # Enqueue a job\\n    job_id = queue.enqueue({\\\"prompt\\\": \\\"bells\\\", \\\"hash\\\": \\\"abc\\\"}, \\\"re