me\":\"run_shell_command\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1777262435390_0\",\"parameters\":{\"command\":\"python -c \\\"with open('sdp/run-log.md', 'a') as f: f.write('| run-t-008@20260427t001208zd-1777260800 | T-008@20260427T001208Zd | claude | gemini | PASS | 450.0s | — |\\\\n')\\\"\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T04:00:35.734Z\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1777262435390_0\",\"status\":\"success\",\"output\":\"\"}\n+[AGENT] Elapsed: 21m 49s / 30m 0s\n+[AGENT] Elapsed: 21m 54s / 30m 0s\n+[AGENT] Elapsed: 21m 59s / 30m 0s\n+[AGENT] Elapsed: 22m 4s / 30m 0s\ndiff --git a/tests/test_generation_queue.py b/tests/test_generation_queue.py\nindex c139620..96a5aa5 100644\n--- a/tests/test_generation_queue.py\n+++ b/tests/test_generation_queue.py\n@@ -256,3 +256,28 @@ def test_dequeue_concurrent_workers_do_not_double_claim(tmp_path: Path) -> None:\n     row = _queue_row(queue, row_id)\n     assert row[\"status\"] == \"running\"\n     assert row[\"attempts\"] == 1\n+\n+class FakeClient:\n+    def generate(self, request):\n+        return {\"audio_path\": \"/tmp/fake.wav\", \"cost_usd\": 0.01}\n+\n+class FakeStorage:\n+    def save(self, result, req):\n+        return None\n+\n+def test_integration_worker_loop_success(tmp_path: Path) -> None:\n+    db_path = tmp_path / \"queue.sqlite\"\n+    client = FakeClient()\n+    storage = FakeStorage()\n+    queue = GenerationQueue(db_path, client=client, storage=storage)\n+    \n+    # Enqueue a job\n+    job_id = queue.enqueue({\"prompt\": \"bells\", \"hash\": \"abc\"}, \"req-1\")\n+    \n+    # Run the worker loop once\n+    processed = queue.process_one()\n+    \n+    assert processed is True\n+    with sqlite3.connect(db_path) as conn:\n+        row = conn.execute(\"SELECT status FROM queue_items WHERE id = ?\", (job_id,)).fetchone()\n+        assert row[0] == \"done\"\ncommit 76efe9b49455224e9d103c63e2e9cde10511882a (HEAD -> feat/graceful-degradation)\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sun Apr 26 20:37:52 2026 -0700\n\n    verify(T-008@20260427T001208Zc): PASS\n    \n    All 9 queue tests pass, 3661/3661 full suite green. Atomic dequeue via\n    BEGIN IMMEDIATE, FIFO ordering, retry/exhaustion transitions, and\n    concurrent no-double-claim verified. Two minor test coverage gaps noted\n    (non-blocking). bootstrap_identity hardening checks flagged as inapplicable\n    to this task.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\ncommit 4e685a629e46671a9e109b36e086a2bdb65bf0ad\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sun Apr 26 20:34:20 2026 -0700\n\n    docs(generation): record queue transition status [T-008@20260427T001208Zc]\n\ncommit 9b2e27e3939eb7f6c8129bd0f15f98fa9af81f38\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sun Apr 26 20:32:30 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(generation): add queue claim transitions [T-008@20260427T001208Zc]"}
sdp/runner.log:6332:{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-04-27T04:02:21.101Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777262540515_0","status":"success","output":"# Changelog\n\n## Unreleased\n\n- Added generation queue claim transitions: `GenerationQueue.dequeue()` now atomically claims the oldest queued row in a single SQLite transaction, marks it `running`, increments `attempts`, and refreshes `updated_at`; `mark_done()` completes running items; and `mark_failed()` requeues transient failures until the retry budget is exhausted, then marks the item `failed`. New queue tests cover FIFO claim ordering, retry-on-failure, terminal failure, timestamp refreshes, and concurrent no-double-claim behavior.\n\n- Added a live Replicate smoke test for the generation backend (T-005): `tests/test_generation_live_replicate.py` exercises `ReplicateClient.generate(req)` against the real Replicate API with a fixed prompt and seed, and asserts a >100 KB WAV payload, `cost_usd` inside `[$0.01, $0.50]`, and `latency_ms < 60000`. The test is gated behind both the new `--run-live-replicate` pytest flag (registered in `tests/conftest.py` alongside the existing `--run-live-modal` seam) and a non-empty `REPLICATE_API_TOKEN`, so the default `pytest tests/` run skips it. Documented as ~$0.10 per opted-in run.\n\n- Added a local Ada generation backend stub: `senseweave.generation.client_local.LocalAdaClient` now satisfies the shared `GenerationClient` Protocol shape while raising `NotImplementedError(\"LocalAdaClient: GPU not yet installed; use Replicate or Modal\")` until the local GPU path is installed. Added focused tests and an explicit mypy check for Protocol satisfaction.\n\n- Implemented `ModalClient` satisfying `GenerationClient` Protocol in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_modal.py`, enabling CypherClaw to use Modal serverless for generation (CCG-012). The client computes A10G runtime cost from metadata and gracefully degrades when the `modal` SDK is not installed. Also added protocol parity tests and gated live Modal tests behind `--run-live-modal`.\n\n- Added a manifest-driven CCS-032 library migration path: `my-claw/tools/sample_library_import.py` now imports single files and directory buckets into `samples/library/`, `senseweave.sample_library.SampleRecord` / `SampleLibrary` now preserve full-record provenance via serialized record storage (including `extras.original_path` and `extras.captured_by`), `tests/test_sample_library_import.py` locks the importer contract, `sample_manifests/anthony-library.toml` captures Anthony's real 101-sample migration plan, and the resulting local library import is kept out of git via `.gitignore`.\n- Added the missing CCS-028 sample-usage journal seam for tracker pieces: `senseweave.usage_journal` now serializes the richer per-piece sampler fields (`started_at`, `mode`, `samples_used`, `transformations`, `clicks`) while preserving the legacy `timestamp` / `samples_played` aliases, `music_tracker_runtime.ScheduledTrackerEvent` now carries sample-gesture metadata through playback emission, `duet_composer.py` now records actual emitted sample-lane events into the post-piece journal hook, and new regression coverage in `tests/test_usage_journal.py`, `tests/test_music_tracker_runtime.py`, and `tests/test_usage_journal_integration.py` composes a short score-tree piece end to end and proves the written journal entry contains populated sample usage, transformations, and arc payoff data.\n- Added focused regression coverage for the operator-diagnostics sampler line (`OperatorDiagnostics.sample_source`) in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics_sample_status.py`, pinning the four discrete states the formatter must produce: sampling-only renders `currently sampling …` without a playback fragment, playing-only renders `playing sample …` without a sampling fragment, both-active joins the two phrases with ` · `, and the all-idle case degrades to `unavailable` so the daemon never serializes an empty sampler line.\n- Added a repo-backed `inkplate_display.py` renderer seam for the sampler status surface: it reuses `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` so the e-ink display follows the same combined plan+playback wording as the face display, and it truncates long sampler lines against the configured e-ink text width with Pillow-based measurement plus `...` instead of letting them overflow. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_inkplate_display.py` for helper wiring, width-fit truncation, fit-without-truncation, and empty-state degradation.\n- Wired the combined sampler plan+playback status line into the face display renderer so the small face monitor mirrors operator diagnostics: added `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` as a thin wrapper that opts into `combine_activity_and_playback=True`, and updated `my-claw/tools/face_display.py` to call it in place of the legacy either/or `sample_status_text(...)` while preserving the existing 24pt centered placement and degradation guards. Coverage in `tests/test_face_display_sample_status.py` pins the combined wording, plan-only fallback, monitor-offline degradation, and the renderer call site.\n- Operator `/status` sampler diagnostics now combine sampler plan and active playback into one human-readable line when both `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` are present, while leaving the face-display sampler wording on its existing playback-first contract; added regression coverage in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py`, `tests/test_sample_status.py`, and `tests/test_musical_integration_runtime.py`.\n- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.\n- Added a piece-aware sampler cast-planning seam: `senseweave.cast_planner` now exposes `assemble_cast(...)`, which derives selector kwargs from a piece fixture (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`/`patch_name`), returns assembled cast entries, and mirrors any pre-selected sampler summary onto the sampler cast entry as `sample_record`; sampler summaries now also derive `duration_sec` from capture-shaped records via `frame_count / sample_rate`, and `duet_composer._get_cast()` now routes through the shared cast assembler. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_cast_planner.py` for fixture-piece planning and capture-shaped sample summaries, while keeping the targeted `cast_planner` + `sampler_dispatch` suites green."}
